"a.迅速消失的，短暂的 【英】 adj. 迅速消失的, 短暂的(vanishing; ephemeral; transient ) 【考】 evanescent : disappear / pliant : yield(短暂的容易消失/柔 顺的容易屈从)evanescent : permanence / archaic : currency(短暂的不持久/陈旧 的不流行)反义词：lasting(长 久的); perpetual(永久的); permanent(持久的) 【记】 e+van(空)+escent(开 始…的)→出现就空了 →短暂的；注意escen t组词：adolescent( 青少年的); efflorescent(开花期 ); senescent(年迈的) 【例】 as evanescent as snowflakes on a river adj. (象烟雾一样)渐渐消失的; 短暂的 = ephemeral = transient 【记】e出, van空, escent开始...的－出现就开始空了－渐渐消失的e出, van = wan完, escent－出去就完蛋了－短暂的 【参】adolescent(adj 青少年的; n 青少年); efflorescent(adj 开花的n 开花期); senescent(adj 老了的) 【类】evanescent: disappear = pliant: yield 短暂的容易消失 = 顺从的容易屈从evanescent: permanence = archaic: currency短暂的不持久 = 陈旧的不流行convoluted: complexity = transient: evanescence费解的是复杂事物的特征 = 短暂的是瞬息的特征periodic: recur = evanescent: vanish 周期的导致重现 = 短暂的导致消失 【反】lasting = perpetual = permanent = abiding(adj 持久的) 【记】e 出，外 + vanish 消失，一出去就消失→短暂 【相关】evanesce 消失，消散 evanescent (adj.)  1717, from French évanescent, from Latin evanescentem (nominative evanescens), present participle of evanescere ""disappear, vanish,"" from ex- ""out"" (see ex-) + vanescere ""vanish"" (see vanish)."
